==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sawfly
<hw>Saw"fly`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of numerous species of hymenopterous insects belonging to
the family <fam>Tenthredinidae</fam>. The female usually has an
ovipositor containing a pair of sawlike organs with which she makes
incisions in the leaves or stems of plants in which to lay the eggs. The
larvae resemble those of Lepidoptera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sawhorse</ent>⟦br⟧
